<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korean Political Parties Hail Amnesty to Former Presidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, December 20 (Xinhua) -- South Korean political parties
Saturday hailed the decision by President Kim Young-sam to grant a
special amnesty to imprisoned former presidents Chun Doo-hwan and
Roh Tae-woo, describing it as a turning point for national
reconciliation and overcoming current financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The presidential office Saturday announced Kim's decision to
grant amnesties to Chun Doo-hwan and Roh Tae-woo and restore their
citizen rights.
</P>
<P>
The Grand National Party, the ruling camp, wished the forthcoming
amnesty would become a turning point of for national unity and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The National Congress for New Politics, whose leader Kim Dae-jung
has been elected as next president of the country, said the amnesty
will help the nation overcome animosity and social clashes.
</P>
<P>
The New Party by the People wished the amnesty would be a turning
point for defeating the country's current financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The presidential amnesty, which will also go to 23 other
prisoners involving in the 1979 military coup, or other misdeeds,
will be effective from December 22.
</P>
<P>
Chun and Roh, top leaders of the 1979 military coup, were
separately sentenced to life imprisonment and 17 years in jail in
last April because they were charged with mutiny, treason and
embezzlement of public funds when they were in power.
</P>
<P>
The pardon is aimed for a grand national unity when the country
desperately needs combination of all forces to overcome the
current financial crisis, said a spokesman of the presidential
office.
</P>
<P>
South Korea is currently in a serious financial crisis caused
by the collapse of a slew of conglomerates and bad loans of
financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
However, under the amnesty, the two jailbirds have to
respectively return 220.5 billion won (about 150 million
U.S. dollars) and 262.8 billion won (about 180 million
U.S. dollars) they illegally amassed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
