<HEADLINE> 2 Injured as Train Derails in Central Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Two people were slightly injured
this afternoon when a train carrying 198 passengers derailed near
Lamia, central Greece.
</P>
<P>
The train, belonging to Hellenic Railways Organization (OSE),
crashed into a boulder that had fallen onto the track during a
rockslide.
</P>
<P>
After the accident, the Thessaloniki-Athens route was closed for
repairs while passengers were transported by coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
