<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Skyway Pilots Begin to Strike for Pay Hike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Pilots seeking higher pay
went on strike against Skyway Airlines early Saturday, grounding
flights at 24 airports in the Midwest of the United States.
</P>
<P>
The strike began after talks on new contract broke down and no
date has been set for the resumption of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Skyway pilots are among the lowest paid in the industry with 50
percent earning less than 16,000 U.S. dollars annually, the Air
Lines Pilots Association said.
</P>
<P>
Skyway is a subsidiary of Midwest Express Airlines. It serves
24 airports in Wisconsin, Michigan, Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky,
Tennessee, Missouri, Ohio, Iowa, Nebraska and in Toronto, Ontario.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
