<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Ministries Urged to Formulate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 20 (Xinhua) --A senior Zimbabwean government
official today called on various ministries to work out coherent
mission and strategic perspectives to guide their programs and
daily activities.
</P>
<P>
The call was made today by Chief Secretary in the presidential
office, Charles Utete, when he addressed participants from
different ministries attending a two-day strategic directions
workshop held by the Ministry of Mines, Environment and Tourism
in Juliasdale in east Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Utete said that it is also necessary to have appropriate
legislation in ministries like that of mines, environment and tourism
that resolves issues of environment protection which is paramount to
the sustainability of the country's natural resources.
</P>
<P>
''Without strategic perspectives that guide us in our work and
where we are headed, we are no different from a rudderless
ship,'' he stressed.
</P>
<P>
It is in light of such considerations and having regarded to
the government's overall reform program that the cabinet last
year invited all ministries to formulate and present to the
review panel how government programs and mission statements can
be successfully implemented. 
</P>
</TEXT>
