<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Values Its Ties with Sri Lanka: Acting President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Acting Pakistani President
Wasim Sajjad said here Saturday Pakistan attached great importance
to its relations with Sri Lanka which are rooted in history.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with visiting Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga, Sajjad said that a strong and stable Sri Lanka would
be a source of stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan president arrived here Saturday on a three-day
official visit to Pakistan. Sajjad expressed the confidence that
her visit will further strengthen the bonds of friendship which
exist between Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Sri Lanka shared common interests in maintaining
peace and stability in the region, the Acting President added.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan president said the Pak-Sri Lankan relations had
traditionally been strong and that the two countries had
cooperated on various issues at the international fora as well as
in the South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
She said: "Sri Lanka has enhanced its relations with Pakistan
over the years and these relations have been greatly strengthened
particularly in the last few years."
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan president said they were happy at the resumption
of dialogue between Pakistan and India and hoped that it would
lead to the resolution of outstanding issues between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka would always be cooperative in promoting this
process, she added.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga also said there are great potential existing
between the Pakistan and her country for enhancing cooperation in
the fields of trade and investment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
