<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-20 18:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Emir Opens 18th GCC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah today opened the 18th summit of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) by calling for "collective defense" to
deal with dangers in the region.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, the emir called on his GCC
colleagues to realize the principle of collective defense "and
total military build-up to our capabilities in order to withstand
dangers."
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the six GCC member states - Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman,
Qatar, Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates (UAE) - began
their three-day meeting to discuss a host of issues of political,
economic and security concerns.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti emir said "the concept of security to our people
and our countries ... is based on the defense of our lands, the
preservation of our society, and the protection of our wealth."
</P>
<P>
He said the GCC states would continue to commit themselves to
preservation of international norms based on mutual respect and
peace.
</P>
<P>
He said GCC states have chosen a comprehensive peace in the
region as a strategic option, and blamed Israel for the stalemate
of the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"We appeal to the family of nations of the world to play a
decisive role and stand up to the policies of Israel," he said,
adding that peace cannot be achieved except by the return of all
occupied territories and the establishment of a Palestinian state
with Jerusalem as its capital."
</P>
<P>
He accused Israel of failing to commit itself to peace
agreements signed with the Arab states, and of bringing the peace
march to a standstill by continuing the construction of
controversial Jewish settlements.
</P>
<P>
Turning to relations with Iran, he said "I felt that a new era
has begun to emerge in our neighborly relations, based on
brotherhood, mutual respect and non-interference in internal
affairs and rejection of the use of force or the threat to use it.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the disputed islands between Iran and the UAE near
the strategic Strait of Hormuz, he reiterated a call on Tehran to
resolve the issue through peaceful channels.
</P>
<P>
The emir also accused Iraq of evading to comply with the U.N.
resolutions pertinent to its 1990 invasion of the small Gulf
emirate.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the cause of the sufferings of the Iraqi people
under U.N. economic sanctions to Baghdad's tactics, saying "we
sympathize with them (Iraqi people) and hope that the reasons for
the continuation of their suffering will disappear by the
regime's compliance with all relevant resolutions."
</P>
<P>
After the opening ceremony, the GCC leaders went into a
closed-door session and due to resume deliberations of the agenda
on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
