<HEADLINE> Egypt Asks Qataris to Get Entry Visas in Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Egypt told Qatar today that
Qatari nationals who want to go to Egypt must apply for entry
visas in advance starting from Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari news agency (QNA) monitored here quoted a statement
of the Egyptian Embassy in Doha as saying that "Egyptian
authorities related decided to issue entry visas in advance to
bearers of all categories of Qatari passports starting from
December 21, 1997."
</P>
<P>
The Qatari government asked its citizens to "get required visa
before departure (for Egypt)" shortly after the issue of the
Egyptian statement, QNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Previously, Qatari people could obtain entry visas after they
arrived in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said the change indicated that the two countries
failed to improve their relations despite the mediation of Saudi
Arabia earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and Qatar's Emir Sheikh Hamad
Bin Khalifa al-Thani held talks in Riyadh, capital of Saudi
Arabia, in a bid to end a war of words between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries deteriorated in October
when Egypt was ready to boycott the fourth Middle East and North
African economic conference in Doha.
</P>
<P>
Qatar responded with a ban on the entry of Egyptian nationals
alongside other nine countries as a security precaution for the
Doha conference, infuriating Cairo and other Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Adding fuel to their row were Qatar's charges that Egypt had
plotted the 1996 coup attempt to topple the Qatari government.
Cairo denied the charges and demanded for an explanation.
</P>
<P>
After the talks of their heads of state, both Egypt and Qatar
claimed that their relations were improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
