<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Arrives in Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived here this afternoon from
Beirut for a two-day official visit to Syria.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival at the airport, Qian told reporters that he
was very glad to visit Syria, the second leg of his Mideast tour
which has taken him to Lebanon, and will take him to Israel, the
Palestinian self-rule areas and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
China and Syria are friendly countries whose peoples are linked
together by a deep friendship, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
He added that since the two countries established diplomatic
relations in 1956, their friendship and cooperation have developed
satisfactorily, and their mutual support on international and
regional issues was useful to both sides.
</P>
<P>
During his visit he would hold talks with his Syrian
counterpart Farouq al-Sharaa on ways of developing bilateral ties,
and on the latest developments in the Middle East peace process
and other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Qian hoped that his current visit to Syria would contribute to
developing and confirming the ties of friendship and cooperation
between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
