<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Studying How To Modernize Its Traditional Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- China's tradition medicine
(TCM) has a goal of modernizing all its enterprises by the year
2020, according to a national conference on reforms and
development of State-owned TCM enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese traditional medicine has entered the best period for
development," said Zhang Wenkang, director of the State
Administration of Chinese Traditional Medicine, who told the
conference, which opened in Beijing today, that modernization will
help TCM enter the world market with confidence.
</P>
<P>
He said that to fulfill its goals for the next century, China
should try to improve the TCM industry by restructuring it within
three years.
</P>
<P>
To do so, 50 of the most promising enterprises will be given
more support for reforms and development so that a modern
enterprise system can be established in them by the end of the
century, he said. Cooperation of agriculture and TCM production
can be increased and sales promotion of TCM products should be
improved, he suggested.  
</P>
</TEXT>
