<HEADLINE> Beijing Stun Sichuan in Chinese Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Ducks stunned Sichuan
Pandas 70-65 in a ninth-round match of the Chinese Basketball
Association first division league here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Pandas held most of the possession of the game but lost their
forms midway into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Ba Teer, who paired with Shan Tao for Ducks' double-center
tactics, scored eight of his 12 points in the first half, and
grabbed the game-high 15 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan missed seven of eight attempts in their free-throws for
a 35-all tie before the breaker.
</P>
<P>
The Ducks made a late 15-0 run midway in the second half after
Pandas clawed back for 47-50 by scoring 11 points in a row.
</P>
<P>
L. Arstone of Ducks and Zhu Dong of Pandas led their teams in
scoring, both 19 points.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, the Chinese Army edged Shandong Baoyuan 81-78
as the winning squad scored six three-pointers out of 21 attempts.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Nangang lost to Guangdong Hongyuan 83-85 as its coach
Xia Hongfa lamented poor defense against the long-distance
attempts as the visiting squad scored 14 out of 28 three-pointers.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Hunters defeated Shanghai Oriental 70-66, while
Zhejiang Zhongxing was blanketed by Airforce Eagles 73-59 for the
biggest victory of the day. The eagles achieved their edge of
46-29 at half break as Liu Tie scored the most of 33 points.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Army beat Jinan Army 75-60 thanks to the home fans.
</P>
</TEXT>
