<HEADLINE> Large Advertisements on Shanghai's Nanjing Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of businesses are
competing for advertising rights on Shanghai's Nanjing Rd.,
reputed to be the busiest shopping street in China, but a
10-million-yuan (about 1.2 million US dollars) neon extravaganza
seems to have taken the prize.
</P>
<P>
The 540-sq.m. ad, which has 4,500 tubes, belongs to the
Rongshida Group of Hefei, Anhui province, which claims to have the
largest sales of washing machines in China.
</P>
<P>
Tobacco companies and foreign businesses have been barred from
advertising, to protect public health and domestic name-brand
products, according to the local advertising management department.
</P>
<P>
Rongshida expects to sell 1.7 million washing machines this
year. 
</P>
