<HEADLINE> Grand Finale Marks 50th Founding Anniversary of HK CSS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Council of Social
Service (HKCSS) held a Golden Jubilee Grand Finale here today to
celebrate its 50th founding anniversary as well as the 5th
anniversary of the International Day of Disabled Person.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China, accompanied by his wife,
Betty Tung, and some SAR government officials, attended the Grand
Finale, which was televised to the public.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of the finale is a Guinness Record breaking
dragon dance.
</P>
<P>
After an eye-dotting ceremony officiated by Tung, the
8,088-feet (about 2,450 meter)-long dragon was brought to live by
4,000 participants from all walks of life, including government
officials, disabled people as well as people from public and
business organizations.
</P>
<P>
Harry Fang, chairman of the organizing committee of the Grand
Finale, said that the Guinness Record breaking dragon dance
symbolizes an ensemble of various parties who are striving for the
betterment of social service in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This year is also the 5th anniversary of the International Day
of Disabled Person. Apart from organizing the lion dance teams,
people from 18 District Offices of the International Day of
Disabled Person also participated in the dragon dance.
</P>
<P>
A total of 38 people were presented the HKCSS Award for their
outstanding social service in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
HKCSS has been representing and working together with Hong
Kong's non-government social welfare organizations in advocating
for the development of social policies and service since its
founding in 1947.
</P>
<P>
It works in concert with voluntary welfare organizations,
service clubs, community groups and individuals, through its 2,500
member agencies to maintain over 80 percent of Hong Kong social
service to various people.
</P>
<P>
Children, youth, community development, disabled and elderly
are all the service targets of the Council.
</P>
<P>
With its unending care and unchanging promise, the Council
always endeavors in forgoing a caring community for the
needy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
