<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Shenhua Snaps Dalian Wanda's Winning Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Shenhua exploited
its home advantage to beat Dalian Wanda 4-2 on Sunday, bringing in
an end to the latter's 55 straight wins in the last round of the
Chinese Soccer League which Wanda had won five rounds earlier in
advance.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua scored its early two goals in the first six minutes
with a left-wing opener through its import player and a loop in
front of the goal mouth by Qi Hong.
</P>
<P>
The visiting squad geared up its attacks through both wings and
was awarded a penalty kick in the 13th minute as a defender of the
home side was caught of tackling from behind within the box.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao converted from the spot before his foreign teammate
kicked home the equaliser six minutes for Wanda who boasted of its
winning streak to 55 matches and has won the league with five
rounds remained.
</P>
<P>
At the deadlock of 2-2, Fan Zhiyi, captain of Shenhua, was
booked with a red card for his arguement with the referee and the
match was suspended for seven minutes as the home fans threw in
bottles of mineral waters.
</P>
<P>
After the interruption, Shenhua who played one man down in the
last 70 minutes, managed for two more goals in the 34th and 40th
minutes respectively through a left-footer off Wu Bin and a header
from another imported player off a corner kick.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua successfully blocked a few attacks from Wanda in the
second half and kept its 4-2 advantage till the end of the match.
</P>
<P>
Chi Shangbin, head coach of Dalian Wanda, hailed the
performance of his opponents and contributed the failure of his
squad to tiredness.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Tianjin Samsung was relegated to Division B
after its defeat of 0-2 in the away game against Jinan Taishan,
while Guangdong Hongyuan met the same fate after being tumbled 1-2
at home by Qingdao Hainiu.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Appolo tied with Sichuan Quanxing 1-1 with all the
goals crowded in the first half, Beijing Guo'an defeated Yanbian
Aodong 2-1, and August First downed Vanguards 3-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
