<HEADLINE> Wild Animals Seek Shelters in Iran's Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Due to heavy rain and
snow in this cold winter, wild animals are leaving their
natural habitats and seeking shelters in nearby villages and
towns, the Iranian official news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
A large number of wild animals are spotted near villages
and towns in Iran's northern province of Gilan to search for
food following a sharp fall of temperature.
</P>
<P>
Iranian environmental protection groups and officials have
urged the people to help the wild animals by offering
necessary food and taking measures to protect them from being
hunted.
</P>
<P>
Iran's Green Front, a environmental protection body, today
also issued a statement calling for assistance to the wild
animals fleeing from the cold mountains.
</P>
<P>
This winter is much colder with more rain and snow in the
northern part of Iran. The Iranian capital of Tehran was also
attacked by the unexpected cold winter. 
