<HEADLINE> Chinese Communist Party Official Calls For A Cleaner Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese Communist
Party leader has called for severe penalties for people who dare
to use their positions for personal gains.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau
and member of the Secretariat of the Party's Central Committee,
made the remark at a national conference on Party organization, in
Beijing today, where he urged the prevention of "unhealthy
tendencies" in selecting officials, including nepotism and
currying favor with people in key posts.
</P>
<P>
"We must in no case appoint people who go against the Party
line, or those who only care for personal interests or who do not
abide by Party discipline and do nothing serious," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hu called on Party committees and leading officials to adhere
to the Party's principle of standards for leading officials and to
choose such officials in a fair way, and especially in promoting
outstanding younger ones.
</P>
<P>
"We must try to create an open, equal, and competitive
environment for selecting personnel to provide institutional
guarantees that allow outstanding people to show their ability,"
he said, and that recommendations from ordinary people must be
considered by the Party in appointing leading officials, and the
assessment system must be improved.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that the the Party should have stricter discipline,
something that should start with leading officials.
</P>
<P>
Party organization officials from across the nation were
present at the conference, which was presided over by Zhang
Quanjing, head of the Organization Department of the CPC Central
Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
