<HEADLINE> Thirteen People Die in Cold Spell in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people have died in
cold spell sweeping across Bangladesh during the past two days,
local press reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Three people died on Saturday, and ten died on Friday, mainly
in the northern districts of the country.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city, where the lowest temperature was recorded
at 13 degree Celsius Saturday, people were wearing sweaters and
scarves to keep off cold.
</P>
<P>
Weather experts say the cold spell has become unbearable for
people as winds from the northeast and the northwest bringing the
cold continued to remain active.
</P>
<P>
The presence of moisture, a result of the rainfall a week ago,
has added an extra chill to the air, they say.
</P>
<P>
In Bangladesh, where snow is rare, the average highest and
lowest temperatures in winter (from December to February) are 26
degrees Celsius and 13 degrees Celsius respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
