<HEADLINE> Fujian Speeds up Legislation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
Fujian provincial People's Congress in east China has legislated
101 local regulations in the past five years to ensure a sound
legal environment for economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
As a pioneer in reform and opening-up, Fujian also ranks among
the first in terms of legislation in the country.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this October, the economically prosperous
province had drawn up 57 economic regulations, accounting for 56
percent of all the local regulations made in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
