<HEADLINE> Anhui's Investment Brings Due Harvest in Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI. December 21 (Xinhua) -- As a result of increasing
investment in agricultural infrastructure, East China's Anhui
province has led the country in the outpout of major farming
products for several years in a run.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, the leading agricultural province has invested 7.68
billion yuan (960 million US dollars) in agriculture, with an
annual growth rate of 23 percent in the sector. That figure has
increased by 12.5-fold over 1987.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the province has managed to have introduced
350 million US dollars of overseas funds and raised 300 million
yuan from the stock market for the agricultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
As a major producer in the country, the province now enjoys an
annual productive capacity of 27.5 million tons in grain, 250,000
tons in cotton and 1.5 million tons of oil crops.
</P>
<P>
The per capita grain output, oil crops and meat has increased
by 10.4 percent, 20.8 percent and 5.8 percent respectively over
1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
