<HEADLINE> China's Largest Abalone Breeding Base Underway in Southern City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's
largest abalone breeding base is underway in Shanwei City, south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The Jiansheng Abalong Breeding Base, involving a total
investment of 50 million yuan, is designed to cover 80,000
sq.m. of floor space. Total construction is scheduled for
completion in three years when its annual abalone output will
reach 500 tons.
</P>
<P>
For the first phase, 20 million yuan will be used to set up 448
abalone fry breeding pools covering 12,000 sq.m. of water area and
560 breeding pools as well as an abalone feeding plant.
</P>
<P>
With a subtropical weather and a location bordering the sea,
Shanwei City has the favorable natural conditions for developing
marine resources.
</P>
<P>
The said breeding base has been invested by a Macao investor,
who is originally from Shanwei. 
</P>
</TEXT>
