<HEADLINE> 170,000 Laid-offs Reemployed In Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 170,000 laid-off
workers in north China's industrial city of Tianjin have found new
jobs as a result of the local government's re-employment program
this year.
</P>
<P>
The city has promulgated a range of favorable policies on
re-employment for laid-off workers, concerning the exemption or
reduction of taxes and relevant fees and the issue of business
licenses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the city has set up nearly 450 firms in the service
trade to have employed over 18,000 redundant workers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 58,000 laid-off workers have started their
own business with the help of local departments of industrial and
commercial adminstration.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the city's 137 job placement
agencies have interviewed 1.65 million job-seekers, and 350,000
applicants have reached agreement with potential employers. By
now, 23 percent of those have been actually employed.
</P>
<P>
Also, the city has held 66 job fairs specially for redundant
workers, which has helped 20,000 people get new jobs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
