<HEADLINE> Garden City Has More Green Lands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The reason that Nanning has
become one of the country's 12 garden cities is obvious to all
those who have visited this capital of southwest China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the city's area covered by trees has reached
344,000 hectares, with the forest coverage rate standing at 36.3
percent and per capita greenery amounting to nearly seven square
meters.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the city has invested 20 million yuan each
year in urban afforestation, with the figure for 1997 exceeding
100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
At present, Nanning has 12 parks and over 30 gardens across the
city, with three of the parks and 20 gardens built in the last two
years.
</P>
<P>
By now, the city has drawn up a complete set of regulations on
building green land in urban areas. According to a plan, the
city's greenery coverage rate and the average area of green land
for each person will reach 37 percent and 10 sq m by the year
2000. 
