<HEADLINE> California's Jobless Rate Falls to Seven-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, December 20 (Xinhua) -- California's jobless rate
fell to a seven-year low of 5.8 percent in November, the state's
Employment Development Department reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This drop, from 6.4 percent in October, was the biggest single
monthly decline over the past 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts seemed particularly pleased by the report amid
increasing concerns over Asia's economic woes which might hurt
California, the U.S. gateway to Asia.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this week, some economists predicted that Asia's
slowdown would cost the state between 26,000 and 65,000 new
nonfarm jobs in 1998, because it relies heavily on Asia for
exports and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The United States' unemployment rate was 4.6 percent in
November. 
</P>
