<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Market Rallies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) rebound from the previous weekend
close of 3,329.27 to end the week at 3,540.91, showing a sharp
rise of 211.64 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index flared up by 85.27 points to close the week
at 1,536.14 as against the previous weekend close of 1,450.87.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted up at the close of
the week at 342.29 and 145.27 compared with the previous weekend
close of 324.95 and 136.17 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Foreign institutional investors, who had turned heavy sellers
in the previous week and collected enough funds, make sizable
purchases in blue chips last week.
</P>
<P>
Domestic institutions remained in the market by picking up the
heavy weighted index scrips.
</P>
<P>
Operators expressed confidence that the market would even
display firm tendency during the next week as the bulls had taken
over the reigns and likely to enlarge their positions in the last
week of the current year.  
</P>
