<HEADLINE> Thai Senate OKs Bankruptcy Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Senate has approved
the bankruptcy bill, which will give debtors more room to
re-arrange their debts with creditors for business rehabilitation,
instead of an immediate shutdown.
</P>
<P>
However, Senate Speaker Meechai Ruchupan said after the
approval of the bill that some wordings of the bill, which are
drafted based on the U.S. Bankruptcy Law, need revision to suit
the Thai society.
</P>
<P>
The Senate gave its approval of the bill on Friday and it will
become a law after being published in a royal gazette, local media
said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai House of Representatives earlier this week approved
the bill, which was proposed by the Chavalit Yongchaiyudh
government to meet the existing situation in the country.
</P>
