<HEADLINE> Lipinski Wins Women's Singles in Munich </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- World women's figure skating
champion Tara Lipinski defeated Tara Szewczenko of Germany to
retain her Champions Series title in Munich, Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But the world champions in two other events were beaten. Elvis
Stojko of Canada fell on an attempted quadruple jump and was
overhauled by Russia's former European champion Ilya Kulik.
</P>
<P>
Germany's pairs champions Mandy Woetzel and Ingo Steuer were
pushed down to second place by Russians Elena Berezhnaia and Anton
Sikharulidze.
</P>
<P>
World, Olympic and European ice dance champions Pasha Grishuk
and Evgeny Platov proved unassailable, however, turning in one of
their finest performances to parry the challenge of Canadians
Shae-Lynn Bourne and Victor Kraatz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
