<HEADLINE> Jailed Drug Cartel Heads Plead for Leave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Brothers Miguel and
Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela, drug cartel leaders in Cali, pleaded
for permission to be let out of the prison they are in to attend
the funeral of their mother who died Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ana Rita Orejuela de Rodriguez, mother of the two drug
kingpins, died at the age of 81 of heart and lung complications at
a clinic in Cali.
</P>
<P>
The woman had been taken to the intensive care ward because of
the seriousness of her health conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Rodriguez Orejuela brothers are being jailed in the "La
Picota" high-security penitentiary ward in the Colombian
capital. It is not known whether the National Penitentiary and
Prisons Institute will grant them a special permit to see their
mother for the last time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
