<DOCNO> XIE19971221.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Determined to Strengthen Ties with Sri Lanka: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif has expressed the firm commitment to cementing of its
relations with Sri Lanka in all fields.
</P>
<P>
During the talks held here Saturday with visiting Sri Lankan
President Chandrika Kumaratunga, Sharif said Pakistan wanted peace
and security in the region and for this purpose it is necessary to
resolve the core issue of Jammu and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, the
two leaders held wide ranging talks and discussed bilateral
relations and regional and international issues of mutual
interest.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said Pakistan had initiated the dialogue with India. He
expressed the hope that India will reciprocate Pakistan's
seriousness of purpose and address all issues including the core
issue of Jammu and Kashmir in a meaningful and substantive manner.
</P>
<P>
Both Sharif and Chandrika held that the economic and trade
relations between Pakistan and Sri Lanka should be further
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lankan President, who arrived here Saturday on a
three-day official visit to Pakistan, said that there existed
friendly relations of confidence between the two countries and she
looks forward to work closely with Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Sri Lanka signed three agreements on cultural
exchange, scientific and technical cooperation, and for the
promotion and protection of investment.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sharif hosted a banquet Saturday evening in
honor of the Sri Lankan President. Speaking on the occasion, he
reiterated Pakistan's stand for a peaceful solution to the Kashmir
dispute and an intra-Afghan dialogue to bring durable peace to the
strife-torn Afghanistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
