<HEADLINE> Review of Economic News From Mercosur </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The following is a review
of economic news in the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) over
last week.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Southern Common Market (Mercosur) 13th Summit
Meeting was held here December 15, at which the presidents of
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay, Uruguay, Chile, and Bolivia pledged
to strengthen the regional integration process.
</P>
<P>
They discussed the increase to the common
external tariff, the liberalization of the service sector, the common
antidumping regulation, social security and cooperation in
scientific investigation.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed on the full integration of Chile into the
Mercosur institutional structure and its participation in all the
political activities of the bloc.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Direct foreign investment received by Brazil
from January to the end of November this year was 15.945
billion U.S. dollars, the Central Bank of Brazil said.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that in 1998 Brazil will receive 20 billion
dollars in direct investment.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Peru and Chile ratified their bilateral agreement on
the conservation of border markets through an exchange of note on
December 16.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
QUITO -- The Andean Community presented Mercosur on December 16
a new proposal that foresees the elimination of custom tariffs and
other restrictions to strike an agreement of free trade between
the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The Brazilian government will invest 210
million dollars in the ecotourism development program of the
Amazonia, Environment Minister Gustavo Krause said on December
15.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Argentina and Uruguay agreed on December 18 to
create a voluntary magnetic card to speed up the crossing of
border people.
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina and Chile will sign a mining
integration treaty before the end of this year, Argentine
Industry, Commerce and Mining Minister Alieto Guadagni said on
December 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
