<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tentative Agreement Reached Shortly After Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Striking U.S. pilots
reached a tentative contract agreement with Skyway Airlines today
soon after they stopped work.
</P>
<P>
The strike by 135 pilots for the Midwestern airline started at
4:05 a.m. (1005 GMT) for higher wages. As the two sides reached an
agreement on the contract, the pilots returned to work at about
5:30 a.m. But it was not clear what the detail of the agreement
was.
</P>
<P>
Skyway pilots are among the lowest paid in the industry with 50
percent earning less than 16,000 U.S. dollars annually, the union
said.
</P>
<P>
Skyway is a subsidiary of Midwest Express Airlines. It serves
24 airports in Wisconsin, Michigan, Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky,
Tennessee, Missouri, Ohio, Iowa, Nebraska and in Toronto, Ontario.
</P>
<P>
As the strike lasted only one and a half hours, only a few
early morning flights had been delayed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
